      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t really mind it either way, and I\u0027m certainly happy to follow up on this any any other streamlining.\n\nIt\u0027s just that this area of code has reached a pretty high level of baseline complexity, and when that happens I\u0027m usually looking for ways to make the most important control flow decision points stand out from the unimportant ones, the easiest way of course being to delete the unimportant control flow entirely.\n\nThis do-we-allocate-a-sampler check here feels more a flourish than anything that matters, and I\u0027m sure I wrote it back when the code was still growing from nothing, simple enough back then that this check didn\u0027t distract.  We\u0027ve since piled enough subtlety in here that my default assumption is that this if-statement must be important enough like the others to justify its existence, that it must be subtle too.  But it\u0027s not at all.  And the thing that got me thinking about it is that we\u0027re making it now look more important with this longer, commented condition.",
